h3. Workaround
Enable all the plugin modules in the Add-On Manager by:

# Expanding Service Desk.
# Click on 162 of 190 modules enabled.
# Go through and enable each module one-by-one.
# Background re-index

h3. Summary
*Run automation rules as...* cannot be edited

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Go to automations
# Set the default user for this project's automation rules.
# Click on the dropdown or type in a username

h3. Expected Results
Username of another user is displayed 
h3. Actual Results
Error message *The JIRA server was contacted but has returned an error response. We are unsure of the result of this operation.* is displayed.

No error on the logs.

Console shows - *Failed to load resource: the server responded with a status of 404 ()* 

h3. Workaround
Follow reproduction steps clicking on the dropdown, this should return

*Make sure the dialogue box is open*

{quote} The JIRA server was contacted but has returned...{quote}
Via Chrome, select 'View' -> 'Developer' -> 'JavaScript Console'
At the prompt add the following snippet, replacing USERNAME_GOES_HERE with the username in Service Desk
{code}(function (username) {
    var $select = jQuery("#sd-run-as-setting-user-select");
    $select.find(":selected").removeAttr("selected");
    $select.append("<option value='" + username + "' selected></option>");
    jQuery(".sd-run-as-setting-save-button").click();
})("USERNAME_GOES_HERE");{code}

Note: This workaround may not work if the username contains capital letters

h3. Summary

Users are unable to remove any request participant via REST API when the reporter is on that list.

h3. Environment
* CLOUD 3.3.0-OD-1000.564.0
* REST API 1000.445.0
* REST API latest - https://docs.atlassian.com/jira-servicedesk/REST/cloud/#servicedeskapi

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a ticket via REST API where the reporter is listed on the request participant's list. E.g. POST:
{code}https://INSTANCE.atlassian.net/rest/servicedeskapi/request
{
    "serviceDeskId": "2",
    "requestTypeId": "16",
    "requestFieldValues": {
        "summary": "Request JSD help via REST 2",
        "description": "I need a new mouse for my Mac"
    },
    "requestParticipants": [
        "user1",
      	"MyReporter"
    ]
}{code}
# Now try to remove any other participant from the list. E.g. DELETE:
{code}https://INSTANCE.atlassian.net/rest/servicedeskapi/latest/request/JSD-44/participant
{
    "usernames": [
        "user1"
    ]
}{code}

h3. Expected Results

* The user should be removed from the request participant's list.
< OR >
* The error message should be clear on what the problem actually is.

h3. Actual Results

The following error message shows up:
{code}{
    "errorMessage": "Failed to update request participants field, errors: ",
    "i18nErrorMessage": {
        "i18nKey": "sd.request.participants.error.field.update.failed",
        "parameters": [
            ""
        ]
    }
}{code}

h3. Notes:
* Via UI it's possible to remove that user from the request participant's list. 
* The problem only happens when the reporter is also into the request participant's list.

h3.Workaround
Do not add the reporter into the request participant's list.
